                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7452">Tārīkh-i Muẓaffarī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_7452">تاريخ مظفّرى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Alternative title stated in colophon: <title>Akhbār al-salāṭīn</title>
                        </p>
                        <p>Universal history, extending to 1211/1796</p>
                        <p>According to preface, completed in 1209/1794-5</p>
                        <p>Extract consists of accounts for the accession of Nādir Shāh to the death of Aḥmad Shāh Durrānī</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Transcribed by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">G. J. Nicholls</persName>, Judge at <name type="place">Farrukhabad</name>, from a manuscript obtained from <name type="place">Agra</name>
                     </note>
                     <filiation>According to Irvine's note, copied from an original manuscript in the possession of Mahārājah Prabhū Narāyan Singh of Benares (Varanasi)</filiation>
                  </msItem>
